-- Auto-generated from the original hospital.db (SQLite) - imports the original 72 rows
-- directly into the CURRENT (v4) schema: request headers + medicine line items,
-- plus backfilled patients/medicines catalog rows so everything is immediately usable.
--
-- Run this only against a FRESH database that already has the v4 schema
-- (i.e. after db/schema.sql, or after the app has created its tables once).
--
-- Note: MySQL's default collation is case-insensitive, so a couple of the
-- original test patient names that only differ by case (e.g. "Bassu" vs
-- "bassu") collapse into one patients row here. This is harmless - the app
-- looks patients up case-insensitively too, so login/history still work
-- correctly either way.
USE hospital_db;

